        {
            "id": "3688b9864f8a4416aa903",
            "questionText": "A student is using an electric kettle and a toaster simultaneously from a damaged extension cord in their dormitory room. The electric kettle is rated at $!$1800\\,\\mathrm{W}$!$ and the toaster at $!$900\\,\\mathrm{W}$!$. Both appliances are plugged into a $!$240\\,\\mathrm{V}$!$ mains supply through an extension cord that has a resistance of $!$0.5\\,\\Omega$!$. Given that the cord feels increasingly hot, calculate the rate at which heat (in $!$\\mathrm{W}$!$) is produced in the extension cord.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "2b965fde9e5b457282ab1",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by finding the total power drawn by the appliances. You need to combine the power ratings of the electric kettle and the toaster. What is the sum of their power values?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "2700"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "W",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "eea7c9ee923f4e7ea93ba",
                    "stepText": "Now, to determine the current in the circuit, identify the correct formula that relates power, voltage, and current. Which of the following formulas should you use?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ec9334df-1b87-4cde-8ba3-db2e48408a2e",
                        "9b6731ea-3a10-4320-b77b-a729fcfd2577"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = V/R$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = P/V$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = P \\times V$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "7b350d60f982416dbdc39",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you've chosen the correct relationship, calculate the current using the equation $!$I = \\frac{P}{V}$!$. Use the total power from Step 1 and the given mains voltage. What is the current in amperes?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "11.25"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "A",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ec9334df-1b87-4cde-8ba3-db2e48408a2e",
