            "id": "a7525fb762a0457fadf97",
            "questionText": "A plumber is working in a basement with damp patches on the floor using an older, unmaintained electric power tool that has a metal casing. Unbeknownst to him, the tool's live wire has contacted its metal casing. The mains voltage is $!$240\\,\\mathrm{V}$!$. The resistance of human skin is typically $!$500000\\,\\Omega$!$ when dry but reduces significantly to $!$1000\\,\\Omega$!$ when wet. A current of $!$100\\,\\mathrm{mA}$!$ passing through the heart is considered lethal. Calculate the current that would flow through the plumber's body if he were to touch the live casing with wet hands. Based on your calculation, state whether this current is lethal.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "0c1b992d011d4db298b5c",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct relationship between voltage, current, and resistance that you'll need to use for calculating the current. Please choose the right formula.",
